TIMELINE OF EVENTS HAPPENING IN USER'S BROWSER
1. JS File loaded by browser
2. App Component gets created
3. Call geolocation service
4. App returns JSX, gets rendered to page as HTML
  -This entire process occurs far sooner than a result is ever retrieved
  -Long ago the App Component was already rendered
  -No way to wait until the success callback is used

  SOLUTION: CLASS-BASED COMPONENT
...
5. Get results of geolocation
